WEBVTT

00:22.523 --> 00:24.441
Okay, my little herpetologists.

00:24.524 --> 00:26.026
Let's review.

00:26.109 --> 00:28.195
Warm or cold-blooded?

00:28.278 --> 00:29.363
Cold!

00:29.446 --> 00:31.657
- Covered in...
- Scales.

00:31.740 --> 00:34.201
Found on every continent except...

00:34.284 --> 00:36.036
Antarctica!

00:36.119 --> 00:37.996
You are brilliant!

00:38.080 --> 00:39.289
And your snakes are tired,

00:39.372 --> 00:41.834
so please return them to their homes
and we'll return to our textbooks.

00:45.879 --> 00:47.756
I hear your heart beating.

00:47.840 --> 00:52.094
Don't be afraid.
I know you are a good snake.

00:55.222 --> 00:58.433
<i>The attack on the school bus</i>
<i>took my friends' lives...</i>

00:59.059 --> 01:00.477
<i>took my sight...</i>

01:01.562 --> 01:03.188
<i>but I survived.</i>

01:04.606 --> 01:07.150
<i>My father wanted to keep that a secret.</i>

01:07.234 --> 01:11.530
<i>He smuggled me out of Russia to America,</i>
<i>to a boarding school for the blind.</i>

01:12.615 --> 01:14.407
<i>He felt I'd be safe there.</i>

01:15.033 --> 01:19.162
<i>My maternal aunt would check in on me</i>
<i>and he would join me as soon as he could.</i>

01:20.330 --> 01:24.459
<i>Until then, I had every Sunday night</i>
<i>to look forward to.</i>

01:47.107 --> 01:48.942
Did you like it?

01:49.026 --> 01:52.112
<i>I could find you</i>
<i>in the midst of a million violins</i>

01:52.195 --> 01:53.864
<i>if you played just one note.</i>

01:53.947 --> 01:56.617
<i>Maybe three notes. But no more.</i>

01:56.700 --> 01:58.952
<i>How was the food this week?</i>

01:59.036 --> 02:00.537
<i>Don't wrinkle your nose!</i>

02:06.334 --> 02:08.921
I'll have Auntie bring you some vatrushka.

02:09.004 --> 02:12.466
<i>I told my friend I would be with you soon.</i>

02:12.549 --> 02:15.218
Soon. I promise.

02:17.930 --> 02:19.556
I need to be careful...

02:20.598 --> 02:23.852
<i>find a new home, where we'll be safe.</i>

02:23.936 --> 02:26.689
<i>It's like hide-and-seek.</i>
<i>Right now we are hiding.</i>

02:26.772 --> 02:29.024
<i>Can you stay hidden a little longer?</i>

02:29.107 --> 02:31.694
Because of you, I know I can do anything.

02:31.777 --> 02:33.737
<i>You can do anything.</i>

02:34.529 --> 02:35.697
Nina...

02:37.282 --> 02:38.909
listen carefully.

02:41.828 --> 02:44.247
No one can know who you are.

02:44.915 --> 02:49.336
You need to stop speaking Russian
until we see each other again.

02:50.170 --> 02:51.504
<i>Understand?</i>

02:51.588 --> 02:52.630
Yes.

02:54.091 --> 02:56.051
I have one last request.

02:57.427 --> 03:00.263
Play.

03:14.194 --> 03:16.071
<i>He was my lifeline.</i>

03:16.154 --> 03:17.614
And I was his.

03:18.741 --> 03:20.743
Every Sunday, we saved each other.

03:22.244 --> 03:25.998
We shed our skins and plotted the future.

03:27.165 --> 03:30.293
I had escaped the Voi, and he would, too.

03:30.919 --> 03:32.546
We'd fool everyone together.

03:35.048 --> 03:38.802
<i>But then, one day, I was called down</i>
<i>to the headmistress' office.</i>

03:46.935 --> 03:49.646
Nina, your aunt...

03:49.730 --> 03:52.274
she's here because something
has happened to your father.

03:52.357 --> 03:54.234
I'm so sorry.

03:56.194 --> 03:57.529
Ninachka.

03:58.280 --> 03:59.531
Auntie.

04:06.538 --> 04:08.123
There was an accident...

04:09.041 --> 04:10.542
a horrible accident.

04:10.625 --> 04:12.419
Your papa is gone.

04:13.461 --> 04:14.629
He isn't dead.

04:14.713 --> 04:17.257
- He's in hiding from the Voi.
- Ninachka--

04:17.340 --> 04:19.176
Your aunt is here
to take you to live with her.

04:20.552 --> 04:22.846
I can't speak Russian.

04:22.930 --> 04:24.514
I can't go with her!

04:24.598 --> 04:27.517
I'm sorry, Nina.
You have to go home.

04:27.600 --> 04:31.104
But I don't have a home
until he comes and we make one!

04:31.188 --> 04:34.274
I'm sorry, sweetheart,
I know it's been good for you here.

04:38.445 --> 04:42.699
<i>I felt my father was in hiding,</i>
<i>but my aunt believed he had died,</i>

04:42.783 --> 04:45.035
<i>and both of our lives</i>
<i>had changed for the worse.</i>

04:46.286 --> 04:49.289
<i>See, as long as I was in school</i>
<i>and she was watching out for me,</i>

04:49.372 --> 04:50.623
<i>my father made sure money,</i>

04:50.707 --> 04:53.043
<i>more money than she had ever seen</i>
<i>in her entire life,</i>

04:53.126 --> 04:54.795
<i>flowed into her account.</i>

04:54.878 --> 04:57.339
<i>For my tuition, for her attention.</i>

04:57.422 --> 04:59.049
<i>But that was all done now.</i>

04:59.674 --> 05:01.301
<i>What little money was left in the account</i>

05:01.384 --> 05:04.346
<i>wasn't enough to cover the burden</i>
<i>of raising a blind child.</i>

05:04.429 --> 05:06.974
Her name is Nina.
She's my niece.

05:07.891 --> 05:09.684
She is fucking blind?

05:09.768 --> 05:15.065
Be decent. Her father, my brother in-law,
a great man, just died.

05:21.238 --> 05:22.865
<i>I was really lonely then.</i>

05:25.408 --> 05:28.370
<i>For the first time,</i>
<i>my blindness felt like a prison.</i>

05:31.164 --> 05:33.000
<i>- It was cold where I slept.</i>

05:34.251 --> 05:36.419
<i>I rarely spoke to anyone...</i>

05:37.420 --> 05:41.133
<i>except for the babies,</i>
<i>who would come and go.</i>

05:41.216 --> 05:43.426
Believe me,
that picture doesn't do him justice.

05:43.510 --> 05:45.095
Beautiful.

05:45.178 --> 05:47.014
How can his mother not want him?

05:47.097 --> 05:48.848
She's young, a college student.

05:49.724 --> 05:51.518
No, he was meant for you.

05:51.601 --> 05:53.103
We're so lucky.

05:53.186 --> 05:56.106
We never thought, at this point, a baby.

05:56.189 --> 05:57.315
Mmm.

05:57.399 --> 05:58.566
We have his room all ready.

05:58.650 --> 06:01.028
Yeah, of course.
Have you brought the money?

06:01.736 --> 06:03.613
Yes, Abel brought it.

06:03.697 --> 06:07.659
Um, we've... been in the car all day.

06:07.742 --> 06:10.662
-May I use your restroom?
-Oh, yeah, of course. It's upstairs.

06:15.208 --> 06:16.877
The first door, you can't miss it.

07:24.777 --> 07:26.071
What's your name, sweetheart?

07:26.154 --> 07:28.365
Shh.

07:29.199 --> 07:32.118
You can talk to me.

07:41.753 --> 07:43.088
I'm Nancy.

07:52.639 --> 07:54.016
I'm Nina.

07:56.184 --> 07:57.602
Does your mom live here?

07:57.685 --> 07:59.479
No, she's dead.

08:13.660 --> 08:15.203
What the hell is this?

08:16.329 --> 08:18.999
Do you know why I'm here?
I'm a cancer survivor.

08:20.792 --> 08:21.876
Nina?

08:22.585 --> 08:23.836
It's okay, I said she could.

08:23.920 --> 08:27.382
Enough, Nina. Go ask Tamara
to help you with your homework.

08:27.465 --> 08:28.841
She said you are behind.

08:28.925 --> 08:30.385
Couldn't we take them both?

08:30.468 --> 08:32.387
Nance, this... I...

08:32.470 --> 08:34.431
Abel, this child is special.

08:35.348 --> 08:37.642
She... she needs more than this.

08:38.435 --> 08:41.771
I can imagine it's very hard.

08:41.854 --> 08:43.065
It is.

08:43.148 --> 08:45.108
Both her parents have passed.

08:45.192 --> 08:46.276
We'll pay you.

08:50.072 --> 08:52.074
Better for you to take the baby.

09:26.191 --> 09:27.650
We choose her.

09:32.905 --> 09:35.117
If you want her, I can't stop you.

09:36.326 --> 09:38.536
You can provide for her
better than I could.

09:39.162 --> 09:40.872
Only, no one should know.

09:40.955 --> 09:42.624
No one would know anyway.

09:43.250 --> 09:45.085
We'll change her name.
Blank slate.

09:45.168 --> 09:49.214
We'll... we'll make her an American girl.

09:50.548 --> 09:53.593
Do you... do you wanna come live with us?

09:53.676 --> 09:54.802
Yes, I'd like that.

09:54.886 --> 09:57.847
Oh, your eyes are blue as the prairie sky.

09:58.932 --> 10:02.519
Prairie. That's what I'll call you.

10:08.566 --> 10:11.068
Here we go, Prairie!

10:11.153 --> 10:14.030
- Careful, Abel!
- Oh, she isn't going to break.

10:14.114 --> 10:15.407
- Careful!
- Are you, Prairie?

10:15.490 --> 10:17.284
-No.
-No? I can't hear you.

10:17.367 --> 10:18.826
-No.
-I can't hear you.

10:18.910 --> 10:21.204
-No!
-I can't hear you!

10:21.288 --> 10:22.289
No!

10:23.790 --> 10:25.625
Okay!

10:27.585 --> 10:30.046
This is your new home.

10:30.130 --> 10:32.840
Well, Prairie, we take off our shoes here.

10:33.841 --> 10:35.218
Let me help you.

10:35.302 --> 10:38.054
Okay, can I lift this foot?

10:38.888 --> 10:40.557
And lift that foot.

10:46.188 --> 10:48.481
Wow! How is that?

10:48.565 --> 10:49.607
Good.

10:49.691 --> 10:52.360
Feel all the branches on it,
and the leaves.

10:54.154 --> 10:57.448
You're climbing a tree!

10:57.532 --> 11:01.661
"'You don't know what these beans are,'
said the man to Jack.

11:01.744 --> 11:05.832
'If you plant them overnight,
by morning they'll...

11:07.334 --> 11:09.211
Up, up, to the sky.

11:09.294 --> 11:13.548
And if it does not turn out to be true,
you can have your cow back.'"

11:13.631 --> 11:16.008
Okay, we'll go to the next one.

11:35.612 --> 11:37.239
She's sleeping.

11:37.322 --> 11:39.991
She's been doing this
for a couple of weeks.

11:42.577 --> 11:45.872
I'm taping it so we can show a doctor.

11:46.789 --> 11:48.791
She needs a doctor, Nancy.

11:56.674 --> 11:59.761
Honey! Prairie, let go. Prairie. Nina!

11:59.844 --> 12:01.178
Oh!

12:03.681 --> 12:05.558
Prairie believes her father's alive

12:05.642 --> 12:08.811
and sneaking her messages
about where to find him in dreams.

12:08.895 --> 12:11.564
She also believes her dreams
are premonitions,

12:11.648 --> 12:13.941
and that the Russian Mafia are after her.

12:14.025 --> 12:18.154
Kids tell tall tales. I did myself.

12:18.237 --> 12:23.493
Yes, but hers are tales of grandeur
that she believes are reality.

12:23.576 --> 12:24.994
Myths that make her special.

12:25.077 --> 12:27.079
So what are you saying exactly?

12:27.163 --> 12:30.082
Prairie's exhibiting early signs
of serious mental illness.

12:30.833 --> 12:32.794
You don't happen to know
the mental history

12:32.877 --> 12:34.504
of her biological parents, do you?

12:34.587 --> 12:36.464
No. Um...

12:36.548 --> 12:41.303
But I am sure that
when she's been with us for a while,

12:41.386 --> 12:42.429
she's gonna be--

12:42.512 --> 12:44.013
Her new stability is essential, yes,

12:44.097 --> 12:48.393
but the best way to support her, ma'am,
is with the right mix of medication.

12:49.102 --> 12:51.896
But how...
how will medication make her better?

12:51.980 --> 12:54.190
I can't medicate her. She's a child!

12:54.274 --> 12:57.443
- What she needs is love.
- Okay, let me be clear.

12:57.527 --> 12:59.320
Untreated, she gets worse.

13:00.071 --> 13:04.575
Blind children are
extraordinarily imaginative,

13:04.659 --> 13:06.578
but this is different, okay?

13:06.661 --> 13:08.496
We're dealing with a psychosis.

13:10.039 --> 13:13.001
If you'll excuse me, I'm gonna
get some samples. I'll be right back.

13:29.934 --> 13:35.732
Because we've got friends and relatives
far away from here who wanna see you.

13:35.815 --> 13:40.403
And also, I think a good mom should have
a picture of her little girl.

13:40.487 --> 13:42.071
-You ready?
-Yes.

13:42.154 --> 13:45.367
One, two, three.

13:45.450 --> 13:46.784
There we go.

13:46.868 --> 13:49.370
<i>Nina!</i>

14:03.217 --> 14:04.301
Prairie, honey...

14:05.302 --> 14:07.054
have one of these.

14:07.138 --> 14:11.100
It'll make you feel better.
Okay, there you go.

14:12.268 --> 14:13.895
And here's some water.

14:18.441 --> 14:21.235
Good girl. You feeling better?

14:21.319 --> 14:22.320
Mmm.

14:22.987 --> 14:24.739
<i>Okay, how does that feel to you?</i>

14:24.822 --> 14:26.574
Good. Fine, fine.

14:26.657 --> 14:29.744
- Is his collar okay?
- Yeah. It's very nice.

14:30.203 --> 14:31.579
I'm starting to sweat.

14:31.663 --> 14:33.623
The lights are hot, sorry about that.

14:33.706 --> 14:34.957
All right, this is gonna be sweet,

14:35.041 --> 14:37.001
not many grandparents come in
with their grandkids.

14:37.085 --> 14:38.669
She's our daughter.

14:38.753 --> 14:40.922
Open mouth, insert foot. Sorry.

14:41.005 --> 14:43.341
All right, everybody, relax. Looking good.

14:43.424 --> 14:47.178
Prairie, my dear,
toward the sound my voice. Prairie?

14:47.261 --> 14:49.680
Prairie,
toward the sound of my voice, honey.

14:49.764 --> 14:50.807
Yeah, there you go.

14:50.890 --> 14:53.476
<i>I was medicated for 13 years.</i>

14:54.977 --> 14:56.813
<i>It made me feel numb inside.</i>

14:57.730 --> 15:00.650
<i>- But it didn't stop my premonitions.</i>

15:02.110 --> 15:03.528
Nina!

15:04.487 --> 15:06.114
Nina!

15:07.824 --> 15:09.659
Nina!

15:45.570 --> 15:46.487
Papa.

16:05.715 --> 16:07.550
You up, sweetheart?

16:07.633 --> 16:09.552
Yeah, I'm good. I'm up!

16:13.723 --> 16:15.433
Let me see in the light.

16:16.893 --> 16:18.435
Oh.

16:20.605 --> 16:24.942
This time of year is...
is always hard on you.

16:26.611 --> 16:27.653
Hold on.

16:40.667 --> 16:42.544
Let's not tell your father.

16:44.170 --> 16:46.005
<i>The medicine dulled me.</i>

16:46.088 --> 16:48.132
But it didn't stop the dreams.

16:48.925 --> 16:51.553
They just kept coming, for years.

16:51.636 --> 16:54.138
Because they were messages
from my father,

16:54.222 --> 16:55.848
reminding me that he was alive,

16:55.932 --> 16:59.310
that he was waiting for me,
that he was calling for me.

16:59.393 --> 17:02.229
Maybe you dreamed of him
because you missed him.

17:03.230 --> 17:06.317
Hmm, normal dreams
don't make your nose bleed.

17:08.570 --> 17:12.239
The premonitions were powerful
because I could see in them.

17:13.575 --> 17:16.285
Twenty-one wax candles, my birthday.

17:16.368 --> 17:18.079
That's when we were to meet.

17:19.080 --> 17:22.792
The face of a giantess,
surrounded by water.

17:25.294 --> 17:27.129
There's only one place that could be.

17:27.838 --> 17:29.382
I made a plan to go there.

17:30.466 --> 17:31.926
Wait a minute. So you just left?

17:32.718 --> 17:35.930
Come on, she didn't just run away.
Right?

17:37.848 --> 17:38.683
I did.

17:40.935 --> 17:42.895
I knew my father was waiting for me,

17:42.979 --> 17:45.648
that Nancy and Abel
would never understand.

17:47.567 --> 17:50.486
A girl I knew from school
was going to Chicago.

17:50.570 --> 17:53.364
I got her to give me a ride
to the Greyhound station.

17:54.365 --> 17:55.866
And from there...

17:57.702 --> 17:58.995
I disappeared.

19:25.122 --> 19:26.916
Miss, we're closed.

19:28.459 --> 19:30.627
I have to ask you to get on the ferry.

19:30.711 --> 19:32.588
I can't, I'm waiting for someone.

19:32.672 --> 19:34.215
Maybe you've seen him?

19:34.298 --> 19:38.511
He's tall, blonde.
His hair might be gray now, or grayish.

19:39.762 --> 19:41.222
No, sorry.

19:41.889 --> 19:42.932
But, miss...

19:45.309 --> 19:47.019
you have to get on the ferry.

19:56.237 --> 19:57.738
I turned 21 today.

19:58.656 --> 19:59.949
Happy birthday.

20:02.576 --> 20:04.912
I wondered all day what it said about her.

20:06.080 --> 20:07.999
Would you read it to me?

20:08.708 --> 20:11.335
Yeah. But then you have to
get on the ferry.

20:12.586 --> 20:13.713
You gotta go.

20:17.633 --> 20:21.303
"Here, at our sea-washed, sunset gates

20:21.387 --> 20:24.681
shall stand a mighty woman with a torch,

20:24.766 --> 20:27.810
whose flame is the imprisoned lightning,

20:27.894 --> 20:31.147
and her name, Mother of Exiles.

20:32.732 --> 20:36.819
<i>From her beacon-hand</i>
<i>glows world-wide welcome,</i>

20:36.903 --> 20:43.117
<i>her mild eyes command the air-bridged</i>
<i>harbor that twin cities frame.</i>

20:44.576 --> 20:50.207
<i>'Keep ancient lands, your storied pomp!'</i>
<i>cries she with silent lips.</i>

20:51.250 --> 20:53.669
<i>'Give me your tired, your poor,</i>

20:53.753 --> 20:56.588
<i>your huddled masses</i>
<i>yearning to breathe free,</i>

20:56.672 --> 20:59.925
<i>the wretched refuse of your teeming shore.</i>

21:02.219 --> 21:06.057
<i>Send these, the homeless,</i>
<i>tempest-tost to me.</i>

21:06.140 --> 21:09.602
<i>I lift my lamp beside the golden door!'"</i>

21:29.080 --> 21:30.957
<i>I should have gone home...</i>

21:31.958 --> 21:35.336
<i>but I was heartbroken and ashamed.</i>

21:35.419 --> 21:37.046
<i>Too proud.</i>

21:41.425 --> 21:45.096
<i>I didn't wanna give up,</i>
<i>so I devised one last plan.</i>

21:47.514 --> 21:51.268
<i>If I couldn't see my father,</i>
<i>maybe he could hear me.</i>

21:54.021 --> 21:57.149
I would play my violin in the underground
until he stepped off a train,

21:57.233 --> 21:58.943
heard my song, and came running.

22:02.238 --> 22:03.405
And do you know?

22:04.323 --> 22:05.324
My plan worked.

22:07.409 --> 22:09.995
But it wasn't my father who found me.

22:11.663 --> 22:13.207
It was another man.

22:15.668 --> 22:17.545
The man who would change my life.

22:35.312 --> 22:37.314
Oh, hey, later, French.
See you tomorrow.

22:38.274 --> 22:39.441
Right.

23:17.479 --> 23:19.315
We haven't done that in a while.

23:20.649 --> 23:21.609
Mmm.

23:22.359 --> 23:23.945
We can now.

23:26.948 --> 23:28.240
Your eyes...

23:29.491 --> 23:31.118
they're sparkling.

23:35.206 --> 23:37.166
You want breakfast in bed?

23:38.834 --> 23:41.378
Well, of course I want breakfast in bed.

24:02.649 --> 24:03.734
What?

24:05.152 --> 24:06.528
I went on a walk.

24:08.572 --> 24:10.324
Your mom and I could go with you.

24:12.826 --> 24:14.536
Alone. Sometimes, I...

24:14.620 --> 24:16.580
Sometimes I just need to be alone.

24:18.457 --> 24:22.003
The last time you went out on your own,
you came back with dog bites.

24:24.713 --> 24:27.299
And then this thing with
Steve Winchell's teacher,

24:27.383 --> 24:29.551
and now you're hiding things from us.

24:29.635 --> 24:32.179
Look, I know that you're trying
to keep me safe.

24:32.888 --> 24:37.142
And I know that I let you down.
I... embarrassed you.

24:37.893 --> 24:40.354
I'm sorry, but I can't...

24:40.437 --> 24:43.399
I can't live cooped up
in this house all the time.

24:44.983 --> 24:48.945
Maybe the doctor in St. Louis was right,
and we... we took you home too soon.

24:49.030 --> 24:51.573
Maybe you need time in medical care.

24:51.657 --> 24:53.200
-Please don't say that.
-Professionals--

24:53.283 --> 24:54.284
Please, I'm...

24:57.913 --> 24:59.915
I'm sorry that I scared you.

25:02.251 --> 25:03.711
Please don't send me away.

25:06.046 --> 25:08.549
If you talk to that trauma counselor,

25:08.632 --> 25:11.635
the one from the FBI,
the one that keeps calling.

25:11.718 --> 25:14.763
You need someone with experience.

25:16.682 --> 25:19.017
- If I do, can I walk at night?
- Prairie--

25:19.101 --> 25:22.063
On my own.
Just for clearing my head, not to--

25:22.146 --> 25:24.606
It's not safe, Prairie.

25:24.690 --> 25:25.733
One hour.

