31:35.519 --> 31:37.438
Is something wrong?

31:37.521 --> 31:40.732
No, no, actually,
uh, I have good news.

31:40.816 --> 31:43.777
- Ah?
- Really good news.

31:44.945 --> 31:48.449
-I got the call today, from that trust.
-Uh-huh. Uh-huh?

31:48.532 --> 31:50.492
And I got the scholarship.

31:51.743 --> 31:54.788
I can go to any school in Michigan,
for free.

31:54.871 --> 31:57.123
So you don't have to worry about anything.

31:59.418 --> 32:02.337
Nothing, <i>Maman.</i> Not even a cent.

32:04.465 --> 32:06.382
So you're done with Harvard?

32:08.802 --> 32:11.304
Uh, well, I...
I haven't heard back from them.

32:11.387 --> 32:14.766
But this is an option, a really good one.

32:14.850 --> 32:16.977
I just want the best for you, baby.

32:20.271 --> 32:22.107
We'll make it without you...

32:23.108 --> 32:25.277
By the skin of our teeth, we will.

32:25.944 --> 32:27.404
Well, I can drive down some weekends,

32:27.488 --> 32:29.615
and we can go to Carlos'
baseball games together.

32:29.698 --> 32:32.451
Baby, you know I can't go
to those things in my condition.

32:32.534 --> 32:33.952
If you really feel like
you have a condition,

32:34.035 --> 32:35.996
you should let me take you to the doctor.

32:37.622 --> 32:38.540
See?

32:40.250 --> 32:43.253
What am I going to do without you
worrying about me all the time, huh?

32:45.547 --> 32:48.800
Well, that's what I'm saying.
You know, I'll be close.

32:49.801 --> 32:50.802
Michigan.

32:56.808 --> 32:58.351
I'm proud of you.

32:59.603 --> 33:03.356
And you deserve
everything in the world...

33:04.399 --> 33:05.817
and more.

33:07.903 --> 33:09.279
<i>Merci, Maman.</i>

33:12.533 --> 33:14.117
A favor, my star?

33:15.118 --> 33:16.453
Pick up milk?

33:17.120 --> 33:19.706
I can't have my coffee
in the morning without it.

33:19.789 --> 33:22.375
Yeah. Sure.

33:26.838 --> 33:29.132
Hey, hey, French. Hey!

33:29.883 --> 33:31.635
Hey.

33:31.718 --> 33:33.469
Yeah, I thought I saw you there.

33:34.513 --> 33:37.182
So I... I like cold stuff in the cold.

33:37.265 --> 33:38.183
Cool.

33:39.560 --> 33:42.813
You're bringing milk?
That's... that's weird.

33:42.896 --> 33:44.731
Oh, no, uh, I'm not going.

33:49.110 --> 33:53.073
You're worried being at the house with her
will mess up getting into college, right?

33:53.156 --> 33:56.868
Yeah, well, I just got a scholarship,
actually. Full ride.

33:57.494 --> 33:58.495
Wow.

33:59.037 --> 34:00.997
If anyone would, it would be you.

34:02.624 --> 34:06.211
You know, my parents
kind of want me to be you. It's--

34:06.294 --> 34:08.255
- Really?
- Yeah.

34:08.338 --> 34:13.051
Uh, first they wanted me
to be Christine Yee, but...

34:17.013 --> 34:19.725
There's a character clause
for the scholarship?

34:19.808 --> 34:23.144
I mean, I know they have one
for the Mabel Allen.

34:23.228 --> 34:25.772
Wow, you know your shit.

34:26.690 --> 34:28.859
Yeah, it's like...

34:29.860 --> 34:32.988
they think people like us will just
slide into being criminals

34:33.071 --> 34:35.281
unless they specifically prohibit it.

34:35.365 --> 34:36.575
You gotta read up.

34:36.658 --> 34:40.662
Yeah. If I'm caught at a house
with drug deals, it's over, you know?

34:40.746 --> 34:42.706
-Mmm-hmm.
-It's different for someone like Steve.

34:42.789 --> 34:44.207
He's fucking his own life up.

34:44.291 --> 34:47.544
And I'm just trying not to fall into
the default of getting my life fucked.

34:47.628 --> 34:49.504
Well, if that makes sense.

34:49.588 --> 34:50.964
No, that makes sense.

34:52.007 --> 34:53.133
It's just...

34:53.216 --> 34:56.136
Aren't you curious
as to how it ends?

34:57.345 --> 34:59.347
-What, her story?
-Mmm.

34:59.430 --> 35:00.891
No, I... I don't really care.

35:00.974 --> 35:02.809
Her story, but...

35:03.894 --> 35:05.186
Us.

35:05.270 --> 35:10.108
I mean, don't you think that...
she picked us for some reason?

35:14.570 --> 35:19.242
Like, Steve's probably a murderer, and,
uh, Jesse's totally checked out of life,

35:19.326 --> 35:22.621
and Ms. Broderick-Allen is weird and sad,

35:22.704 --> 35:26.082
and I'm... well, you know.

35:27.542 --> 35:28.584
I don't need help.

35:29.169 --> 35:31.797
-No, I know, I wasn't--
-No, I do everything on my own.

35:33.924 --> 35:35.717
I know. I...

35:38.803 --> 35:42.515
Yeah. Well, I gotta get this back
in non-ice cube form. So...

35:43.058 --> 35:44.059
Okay.

36:03.620 --> 36:04.996
Damn it.

36:06.373 --> 36:07.666
Buck!

36:09.334 --> 36:10.501
Buck!

36:20.053 --> 36:21.387
Come on, let's go.

36:33.149 --> 36:34.901
Oh, that's cool.

36:35.652 --> 36:37.654
Got fucking frostbite last night.

36:43.118 --> 36:45.954
If we're gonna keep doing this,
you can't deal outta here.

36:46.037 --> 36:47.414
What's it to you?

36:49.040 --> 36:50.458
You just can't.

36:52.669 --> 36:55.213
Guys, OA said we only have an hour.

36:55.296 --> 36:58.049
-Let's not waste time.
-Whatever, man.

36:58.758 --> 37:01.136
But that means your supply
is cut, too, Buck.

37:01.219 --> 37:02.637
Including the testosterone.

37:18.945 --> 37:20.739
I can tell you everything
that I did wrong.

37:21.740 --> 37:23.575
I didn't eat when I was hungry.

37:23.658 --> 37:25.535
Didn't sleep when I was tired.

37:25.618 --> 37:27.370
Didn't get warm when I was cold.

37:27.453 --> 37:28.704
It made me weak.

37:30.706 --> 37:32.959
But the biggest mistake I made
was believing

37:33.043 --> 37:34.836
that if I cast a beautiful net...

37:36.087 --> 37:37.964
I'd catch only beautiful things.

39:56.394 --> 39:58.479
Your music, it's...

39:59.397 --> 40:01.316
Russian, yes?

40:04.069 --> 40:05.278
Are you Russian?

40:06.321 --> 40:08.531
Me? No. I'm American.

40:08.614 --> 40:09.615
Hap...

40:10.700 --> 40:13.536
...is my name.
Dr. Hunter Aloysius Percy,

40:13.619 --> 40:15.330
so, Hap for short.

40:16.414 --> 40:18.041
Can I... Can I help you with something?

40:18.124 --> 40:19.250
No, no, no.

40:21.502 --> 40:23.004
Can I ask you something?

40:23.671 --> 40:25.465
I'm sorry, I'm late. I have to go.

40:25.548 --> 40:27.425
Did you always play that well?

40:27.508 --> 40:29.219
Or did something happen to you?

40:30.761 --> 40:32.638
It did, didn't it?
Something happened to you and then you,

40:32.722 --> 40:36.142
then you could play...
transcendently like that.

40:37.268 --> 40:40.605
Did... I'm sorry.
Did... did you have an NDE?

40:40.688 --> 40:41.814
I don't know what that is.

40:41.898 --> 40:44.233
Uh, a near-death experience.
Did you die?

40:44.901 --> 40:46.444
Then come back to life?

41:03.003 --> 41:05.130
- You okay with lemon?
- Yeah.

41:05.213 --> 41:07.548
All right. Here we go.

41:07.632 --> 41:09.259
You take this, put it up to your mouth,

41:09.342 --> 41:11.677
and you just slurp the oyster down

41:11.761 --> 41:13.763
like you're sucking sea water
out of a shell.

41:16.557 --> 41:17.767
Oh.

41:21.729 --> 41:23.398
All right, I hated my first one, too.

41:23.481 --> 41:25.650
Uh, can we get some fries, please?

41:25.733 --> 41:27.276
But everything good in this world takes,

41:27.360 --> 41:28.653
uh, getting used to.

41:28.736 --> 41:31.822
Right, I remember my first coffee
in college.

41:31.906 --> 41:33.992
I wanted to throw up.
But by the end of medical school,

41:34.075 --> 41:36.077
I couldn't get out of bed
without a double shot.

41:36.161 --> 41:38.621
That's a lot of school for someone
who said they hated it.

41:38.705 --> 41:41.582
Well, I didn't... I just didn't understand

41:41.666 --> 41:44.960
why I wasn't supposed to ask the questions
that had no answers.

41:45.045 --> 41:47.213
They're the most interesting questions,
aren't they?

41:47.297 --> 41:48.673
What is consciousness?

41:48.756 --> 41:53.678
Where does consciousness go after...
you know, after this place?

41:53.761 --> 41:54.679
Hmm.

41:55.430 --> 41:56.889
But you know. Right?

41:56.972 --> 41:58.058
I mean, when you were...

41:58.141 --> 42:01.769
Let me ask you a question,
when you returned after dying, was that...

42:02.687 --> 42:05.023
Did you feel like that was a choice?

42:05.106 --> 42:07.192
-You experienced it as a choice?
-Yeah.

42:07.275 --> 42:08.859
Wow. Wow.

42:08.943 --> 42:11.529
You called it a near-death experience?

42:11.612 --> 42:12.697
-Yeah.
-So you had one?

42:12.780 --> 42:16.034
Uh, here, ketchup at midnight,

42:16.117 --> 42:18.494
mustard at four o'clock,
mayo at eight o'clock.

42:18.578 --> 42:20.955
Good stuff, okay?

42:21.872 --> 42:23.916
Did I have an NDE? No.

42:24.000 --> 42:26.252
I didn't, but I, uh...

42:28.213 --> 42:31.924
It's pretty much all I...
Well, it is all I think about.

42:32.007 --> 42:33.468
What my life's about.

42:34.385 --> 42:40.266
So I was an anesthesiologist in the ER,
and the first time I heard... uh...

42:40.349 --> 42:42.727
a patient flat-line, I thought...

42:43.436 --> 42:47.440
like, I almost heard... something.

42:47.523 --> 42:48.900
You know? Something...

42:49.609 --> 42:51.944
I don't know. Something.

42:54.363 --> 42:56.199
So I went to this bunch of doctors,
summoned my courage.

42:56.282 --> 42:57.283
I asked them, they're like,

42:57.367 --> 42:59.869
"Eh, yeah, everybody thinks
they feel something."

42:59.952 --> 43:02.997
No, I heard... a whoosh...

43:03.998 --> 43:07.627
of something leaving the body,

43:07.710 --> 43:11.422
and the whoosh... of it coming back.

43:15.468 --> 43:19.054
Now if they came back,
it means they went somewhere.

43:20.390 --> 43:21.641
Where did they go?

43:27.938 --> 43:29.274
We could prove that.

43:31.734 --> 43:32.860
Wow.

43:32.943 --> 43:37.157
I... I did what any reasonable scientist
would do.

43:37.240 --> 43:40.493
I walked away from the ER
and I started what has become

43:40.576 --> 43:45.790
a... a lifetime of study of,
uh, NDE survivors.

43:46.707 --> 43:49.001
So you know people like me.

43:51.629 --> 43:52.630
Yeah.

43:52.713 --> 43:56.759
Yeah, well, I'm... I'm doing a study
right now with three people just like you.

43:56.842 --> 43:59.137
Well, one of them is
particularly like you.

43:59.220 --> 44:02.723
She came back with, uh,
special skills, musical ability.

44:02.807 --> 44:04.099
Like, what is that?

44:04.184 --> 44:08.271
Perfect pitch, in her case,
but there are others I've met who've...

44:08.354 --> 44:09.897
People come back with, uh,

44:09.980 --> 44:14.444
mathematical or artistic, or, you know,
um... linguistic abilities.

44:14.527 --> 44:16.279
It's... It's...

44:16.362 --> 44:17.947
That's not what makes them amazing.

44:18.030 --> 44:20.074
What makes you incredible...

44:21.201 --> 44:25.163
is that you have traveled outside this...

44:26.289 --> 44:28.457
...coma...

44:29.667 --> 44:30.710
that we're all in.

44:31.877 --> 44:33.003
You know?

44:34.755 --> 44:36.090
Ever since I left Russia,

44:36.174 --> 44:39.260
the only thing I've thought about
every day is how to find my father.

44:40.052 --> 44:42.888
And he was the only person
who never made me feel like

44:42.972 --> 44:44.640
I was demented or--

44:44.724 --> 44:45.850
No, of course not.

44:45.933 --> 44:48.394
You should never have been medicated.

44:49.270 --> 44:50.188
Never.

44:50.813 --> 44:53.274
Why, because you're...
you have vivid dreams?

44:53.358 --> 44:54.900
That's insane.

44:58.070 --> 45:00.781
Sorry, this is so strange to hear that...

45:01.449 --> 45:03.826
I am weird, but that you like weird.

45:03.910 --> 45:05.203
No, weird is good.

45:06.912 --> 45:10.124
I mean, there's some pathetically
ordinary guy somewhere

45:10.208 --> 45:11.959
wearing a T-shirt with that
emblazoned on the front:

45:12.042 --> 45:13.753
"Weird is good."

45:23.137 --> 45:25.014
I have to go.

45:26.474 --> 45:27.892
Can I get the check, please?

45:28.518 --> 45:32.522
I have to fly home tonight,
get back to work.

45:32.605 --> 45:33.939
Um...

45:34.690 --> 45:37.610
I have something
I think you might like. Um...

45:37.693 --> 45:39.612
It's kind of an offshoot of my work.

45:39.695 --> 45:43.908
So, I was here, I sold a patent
at a conference yesterday, and...

45:43.991 --> 45:46.619
-Can I show you something?
-Yeah, yeah.

45:46.702 --> 45:48.120
Yeah? Okay.

45:50.623 --> 45:51.707
Here.

45:51.791 --> 45:53.918
Okay, let's get this stuff out of the way.

45:54.001 --> 45:59.549
So, like I said, a lot of it is about
trying to hear the whoosh, okay?

45:59.632 --> 46:04.345
I'm just gonna put that right in there.

46:04.429 --> 46:06.180
Okay, is that in?

46:13.354 --> 46:14.522
-Okay?
-Mmm-hmm.

46:14.605 --> 46:16.106
All right, now...

46:17.567 --> 46:19.193
You switch it on down there.

46:20.611 --> 46:24.532
This can make a heartbeat audible
at 500 feet.

46:25.616 --> 46:27.535
-Just press this?
-Uh-huh.

46:42.508 --> 46:45.011
That! She's move... Someone's moving.

46:45.094 --> 46:46.220
Yeah.

46:52.018 --> 46:53.936
Younger maybe? Like a kid?

46:54.019 --> 46:55.896
Absolutely, absolutely.

46:57.064 --> 47:01.110
You know, a heartbeat is...
is more unique even than a fingerprint.

47:01.193 --> 47:02.362
Here, try this.

47:16.459 --> 47:18.544
- Wow!
- Yeah.

47:34.560 --> 47:36.270
That's what you sound like.

47:38.564 --> 47:40.107
That's what I sound like.

47:48.491 --> 47:49.700
Take me with you.

47:51.243 --> 47:52.495
Study me.

47:54.163 --> 47:55.456
Are you sure?

48:03.548 --> 48:04.549
How long?

48:05.716 --> 48:07.968
No headwinds. Just a few hours.

48:11.764 --> 48:14.183
Put your hands to the right.
There's a window there.

48:14.266 --> 48:18.354
Pull it. Okay, slide it down and back.
There's a latch in the middle.

48:20.106 --> 48:23.067
Keep going, there you go,
and pull it up and over and back.

48:23.150 --> 48:26.612
Up and over and back, all the way.
Push the window.

48:28.072 --> 48:29.532
Push, go on.

48:52.722 --> 48:54.724
Okay, here we are.

48:57.309 --> 49:00.480
Glad I left the heat on. I don't know
what you would've thought of me

49:00.563 --> 49:02.523
if you walked into a freezing house.

49:05.901 --> 49:10.490
Oh, there's a bed downstairs in the lab,
hope that's okay.

49:16.411 --> 49:17.538
It's so quiet.

49:19.081 --> 49:21.000
There aren't any roads nearby?

49:21.083 --> 49:24.461
Uh, that and there's
insulated glazing on every window.

49:24.545 --> 49:26.130
The winters here are brutal.

49:26.213 --> 49:28.508
Glass of water.

49:30.468 --> 49:31.510
Can I use your phone,

49:31.594 --> 49:33.888
just to call my parents
and tell them I'm okay?

49:33.971 --> 49:35.515
Yeah, sure.

49:40.728 --> 49:42.229
Here, let me take that.

49:42.312 --> 49:49.153
And, uh, there's a chair
right behind you now. Okay.

49:52.156 --> 49:53.824
-You want help to dial?
-Oh, no.

49:53.908 --> 49:55.117
Okay.

50:35.407 --> 50:38.744
It just keeps ringing.
They're probably on the other line.

50:38.827 --> 50:42.081
Well, we'll call them again tomorrow.
We don't want 'em to worry.

50:43.332 --> 50:44.375
So...

50:45.125 --> 50:47.086
long day for you, must be tired.

50:47.169 --> 50:48.838
-Can I show you downstairs?
-Yeah.

50:48.921 --> 50:49.964
All right.

50:54.760 --> 50:58.264
Okay, it's two sets of stairs.

50:58.347 --> 51:00.015
First one's the easy one.

51:00.808 --> 51:03.518
There's a handrail on your left.

51:04.687 --> 51:06.355
Okay, got it?

51:07.898 --> 51:10.400
And then there's a spiral coming up.

51:13.862 --> 51:16.448
Okay. Here, you're about halfway down.

51:21.704 --> 51:23.330
Oh... I'll take your bag.

51:23.413 --> 51:25.124
Sorry.

51:26.083 --> 51:27.459
Smells like rock.

51:28.753 --> 51:30.254
Shale.

51:30.337 --> 51:31.714
Here.

51:31.797 --> 51:33.423
I built this lab myself.

51:34.508 --> 51:36.551
Okay, there's a big step coming up.

51:38.804 --> 51:40.055
Is that running water?

51:40.139 --> 51:43.475
Yeah. It's a natural spring.
I just left it.

51:43.558 --> 51:45.811
Never the same river twice, as they say.

51:47.021 --> 51:49.607
And... hold on, here we are.

51:52.735 --> 51:54.111
Okay.

51:54.194 --> 51:56.614
There's a bed three steps ahead of you.
Turn around.

51:57.823 --> 51:58.866
Okay.

52:05.497 --> 52:09.669
You are an incredible asset, Prairie.

52:09.752 --> 52:15.758
I'm... I'm so lucky that I met you,
and to be working with you.

52:18.761 --> 52:20.054
Thank you.

52:24.099 --> 52:25.267
You get some rest.

52:26.101 --> 52:27.186
Good night.

52:59.760 --> 53:00.803
Hap?

53:15.234 --> 53:16.819
Okay, okay.

53:16.902 --> 53:18.404
Let me walk you through this,

53:18.487 --> 53:20.739
'cause I know where your head's at.

53:20.823 --> 53:22.157
"This is not happening."

53:22.241 --> 53:23.408
It is.

53:24.409 --> 53:25.745
"This is a dream."

53:25.828 --> 53:27.662
You are wide awake.

53:27.747 --> 53:29.081
"Someone will find me."

53:30.332 --> 53:32.626
"Why am I locked in a cage?"

53:34.378 --> 53:37.840
Well... you'll find out soon enough.

53:38.465 --> 53:42.886
It may be a while
before he comes for you.

53:42.970 --> 53:46.306
And as you think about
every step that led you here,

53:46.390 --> 53:51.645
you'll eventually realize
it's no one's fault but your own.

53:52.897 --> 53:56.859
Your thoughts are gonna
try to take you down. Don't let them.

53:58.027 --> 53:59.736
You'll find your freedom.

53:59.820 --> 54:01.113
In sleep.

54:01.781 --> 54:03.282
In your dreams.

54:04.741 --> 54:06.701
It's how we stay sane.

54:10.330 --> 54:11.581
What's your name?

54:15.461 --> 54:16.837
Prairie.

54:19.464 --> 54:20.883
Prairie.

54:22.843 --> 54:23.844
My name is...

54:26.346 --> 54:27.514
Homer.
